title: The Neurobiological Sequelae of Distributed Psychological Warfare
summary: This expert report analyzes a four-year case of distributed psychological warfare and its neurobiological impacts, arguing the target's symptoms are trauma responses rather than primary psychiatric illness.

title: Psychological Warfare Manual
summary: A tactical blueprint detailing doctrines, HUMINT structure, offensive maneuvers, and counter-offensive defenses including the Breadcrumb Web and Dead-Man's Switch.

title: Forensic Analysis: The Architecture of Systematic Psychological Warfare
summary: Forensic mapping of systematic psychological campaigns: doctrine, HUMINT network structure, exploitation cycles, and institutional co-option with recommendations for evidence collection.

title: The Unseen Game: The Playbook
summary: A playbook chapter describing "soft probes" and "loyalty tests": reconnaissance maneuvers that collect behavioral intelligence and methods for detection and countermeasures.

title: Civilians as Weapons: The Silent Soldiers of a Setup
summary: Examines how ordinary civilians are co-opted into disinformation and smear campaigns; documents mechanisms, indicators, impacts, and resistance strategies for detection and remediation.

title: Forensic Analysis of Jess: A Study in Relational Duality
summary: Forensic deconstruction of a long-term relationship exhibiting manipulation, DARVO patterns, and the weaponization of housing; includes case studies and countermeasures.

title: Fixing Broken System (transcript)
summary: Transcript discussing correctional reform, the importance of treatment over warehousing, personal rehabilitation via victim-empathy education, and community-based support as recidivism mitigation.

title: Forensic Analysis of Systematic Psychological Warfare
summary: Doctrine-level report on systematic psychological warfare, describing attrition loops, plausible deniability, cognitive degradation, and practical countermeasures.

title: Key Concepts, Relationships, Events, and Insights
summary: Comprehensive mind-map compiling actors, tactics, vulnerabilities, countermeasures, and the Breadcrumb Web framework; serves as a taxonomy for the collection.

title: Long Backstory — Ryan
summary: Autobiographical backstory describing prison-to-recovery trajectory, educational transformation as a tutor, relationship history, and the development of resilience and survival strategies.

title: Ryan Overview
summary: Thematic overview of Ryan's identity, history, relationships, recovery journey, and systemic critiques; useful as a primary profile for the collection.

title: RyanrealAF: Brand & Persona Analysis
summary: Analysis of the `RyanrealAF` brand—psychological, sociological, linguistic, and artistic perspectives—detailing how narrative identity and radical honesty form the brand's core.

title: Skittlez Backstory — Full, Detailed Record
summary: Comprehensive backstory of Skittlez, describing first contact, ritual dynamics, acts of loyalty, and the asymmetric relationship patterns; includes origin story and observed recruitment behaviors.

title: Know the Game: Street Psychology & Social Manipulation 101
summary: A modular curriculum teaching detection and defense against social manipulation: tactics, psychological effects, and practical countermeasures for reclaiming narrative control.

title: The Architecture of Psychological Annihilation
summary: Detailed analysis of how coordinated psychological operations dismantle consensus reality and degrade decision-making; discusses mechanisms and implications for resilience.

title: The Honeypot Doctrine
summary: A transformational narrative detailing the shift from target to asset: how sustained harassment becomes intelligence collection, and how the victim becomes the weapon through strategic reframing.

title: The Infiltrator's Playbook: A Guide to Strategic Reversal
summary: Tactical manual for transforming from target to proactive counter-operative. Outlines Infiltrator doctrine with inverse triangulation profiling, Breadcrumb Web as offensive weapon, and Dead Man's Switch deterrent.

title: The Social Test: A Narrative of Manipulation and Survival
summary: First-person narrative examining systematic social testing and coercion. Documents loyalty tests disguised as assistance, orchestrated setups forcing illegal behavior, and escalating threats in street environments.

title: The Unlikely Classroom of Ryan Borland: A Study in Lived-In Wisdom
summary: Examines how Ryan Borland transformed brutal lived experience into unique pedagogy. Analyzes prison teaching methodology, syllabus of scars (Lacey, Jess, Emily), and crystallization into RyanrealAF gospel.

title: The Unseen War: Surviving Psychological Manipulation
summary: Comprehensive strategic briefing synthesizing non-kinetic psychological warfare doctrine with counter-strategies. Covers HUMINT network model, exploitation cycle, and counter-offensive doctrine including Deep Dive model.

title: The Game Now Seen (Final)
summary: Comprehensive field manual providing tactical deconstruction of systematic psychological operations. Covers doctrine of non-kinetic maneuver, asymmetric HUMINT threat models, and counter-offensive strategies with Three-Step Re-framing Protocol.

title: Content Index: RyanrealAF Master Doctrine Archive & Content Catalog
summary: Comprehensive index and organizational catalog of RyanrealAF Master Doctrine Archive. Provides structured overview of Tier 1 Core Doctrine and cross-references across all doctrinal materials and operational frameworks.
